oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Justin Tubb Press Release: Version 1
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Offset printing; Tubb, Justin;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white negatives taped to and framed by a masking sheet advertising Justin Tubb and containing a biography of his life and accomplishments. The press release describes Tubb's appearances with his father (Ernest Tubb), time in college, work as an emcee at WHIN Radio, first recording contract, songs recorded, hobbies, and personal life. The negative containing the photograph of Justin Tubb is missing. The negatives would have been used to create a corresponding printing plate. This appears to be the first version of the press release, as some information has been updated in version two.
